did.unittitle: Beatrice Binner Papers

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized in one series.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains slides, photographs, maps, guidebooks, notes and newspaper clippings relating to Binner's time working for the American Red Cross. Binner, a 1943 graduate of Jackson College, traveled extensively during her tenure in the Red Cross. For instance, there are numerous photographs of her travels in Libya, Philippines, and Europe from the 1950s and 1960s. Binner's notes and newspaper clippings, such as articles about Muammar Gaddafi's 1970 coup in Libya, provide contextual information about her photographs and the locations in which they were taken.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Beatrice Binner is a 1943 graduate of Jackson College.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Some material in this collection may be protected by copyright and other rights. Please see "Reproductions and Use" on the Digital Collections and Archives website for more information about reproductions and permission to publish. No documentation is available regarding the intellectual property rights in this collection.

did.unittitle: Photographs, slides, and memorabilia

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains photographs, slides, guidebooks, maps, as well as Beatrice Binner's memories of trips overseas while serving with the Red Cross. All titles beginning with "Case" refer to the slides found in that case. Boxes three and four contain kodachrome prints made from the slides found in Boxes 1 and 2.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This series is arranged by her cases, which is loosely chronologically.
